  "title": "BIM MODELLER",
  "description": "<p>Job Responsibilities:</p><p>Create detailed piping drawings, layouts, and isometric diagrams using CAD software.</p><p>Develop and modify piping designs based on engineering specifications and project requirements.</p><p>Ensure compliance with industry standards, codes, and client specifications.</p><p>Collaborate with engineers, designers, and project teams to ensure accurate and efficient designs.</p><p>Review and revise drawings as needed based on feedback and site conditions.</p><p>Maintain accurate documentation and drawing records for project deliverables.</p><p>Assist in material take-offs and bill of materials (BOM) preparation.</p><p>Conduct field visits to gather data and verify design feasibility.</p><p>Requirements:</p><p>Diploma or degree in Mechanical Engineering, Drafting, or a related field.</p><p>Proficiency in AutoCAD, Plant 3D, or other relevant design software.</p><p>Knowledge of piping systems, symbols, and industry standards (ASME, API, etc.).</p><p>Strong attention to detail and accuracy.</p><p>Ability to work independently and in a team environment.</p>",
